{"id":"diversity-world-6","label":"Diversity in the Living World","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"notes","type":"passage","label":"Notes","data":{"title":"Diversity in the Living World","text":"# Types of Plants\n        Some plants grow really tall and have hard, thick, brown, and woody stems. Their branches typically start higher up on the stem and away from the ground. These plants are called trees. \nSome plants are typically small with soft and green stems. These are known as herbs.\nSome plants have hard stems but not very thick. These are known as shrubs.\nSome plants with weak stems need support to climb and grow, and are called climbers. Some plants creep along the ground and are called creepers.\n# Leaves\nThe thin lines on the leaves of the plants are called veins. The pattern of veins on the leaf is called venation.\nIn some leaves, you can observe a net-like pattern of veins on both sides of a thick middle vein. This  pattern is called reticulate venation. eg: hibiscus plant, mango tree, papaya tree.\nIn some leaves, you may observe that the veins run parallel. This pattern is called parallel venation. eg: banana plant, grasses\n# Roots\nSome plants have one main root and small side roots arising from it. The main root is called taproot. eg: mustard plant, hibiscus, chickpea\nSome plants have a bunch of similar-sized thin roots arising from the base of the stem.  Such roots are called fibrous roots. eg: common grass, wheat\n# Seeds\nSoak some chickpea and maize seeds in water for three days. Remove the seed coat and observe the structure. Chickpea seeds are split into 2 parts. Each part is called a cotyledon. Plants that have seeds with two cotyledons are called dicotyledons (dicots). Maize has a single thin cotyledon. Plants with such seeds are called monocotyledons (monocots).\nDicot plants have reticulate venation and taproot system. Monocot plants have parallel venation and a fibrous root system.\n# Movement of Animals\nAnimals can fly, run, crawl, walk, hop or jump, and so on. They use different body parts for moving from one place to another. They may use wings, legs, and other parts that help them to move.\n# Adaptation\nWe have learnt that the plants and animals living in a particular region have special features that make them fit to survive there. The special features that enable plants and animals to survive in a particular region are called adaptations.\nThe fleshy stems of plants found in the desert can store water and help them tolerate the hot conditions in these places. \nThe mountains in extremely cold regions experience frequent snowfall. Conical shape and sloping branches of deodar trees enable them to let the snow slide off easily.\nRhododendron trees have shorter height and smaller leaves to survive through the heavy winds on mountain tops.\n# Habitat\nThe place where plants and animals live is called their habitat. For example, the habitat of sea turtles is the sea or the ocean. The habitat of a camel is the hot or the cold desert, and the habitat of a rhododendron is the mountains. \nThe plants and animals that live on land are said to live in terrestrial habitats. eg: forests, deserts, grasslands, and mountains\nThe plants and animals that live in water are said to live in aquatic habitats.eg: ponds, lakes, rivers, and oceans\nLiving things that can live in both land and water are called amphibians. eg: Frog\n# Protecting Habitat\nThe damage to habitats of plants and animals results in loss of their homes, food, and other resources. This leads to the loss of biodiversity.\nThe population of the Bengal Tiger, Cheetah, and Great Indian Bustard has declined in India due to loss of natural habitats caused by human activities. The Government of India has initiated several projects to conserve our biodiversity. ‘Project Tiger’ was initiated in 1973 to protect the declining population of the Bengal Tiger. The ‘Cheetah Reintroduction Project’ was initiated in 2022 to restore the population of the Cheetah.\nSimilarly, habitats of the Great Indian Bustards have been declared as Protected areas in the states of Gujarat, Rajasthan and Maharashtra.\n# Sacred groves\nSacred groves are undisturbed patches of forests. Their sizes may vary from quite small to very large. Sacred groves are found all over India. They are home to different kinds of plants and animals, including numerous medicinal plants. These are protected by the local community and no one is allowed to harm any animals and cut trees in these groves, or disturb the area. This way, sacred groves are a community protected treasure of biodiversity."}},{"label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"matchByDragDrop","id":"fillup","onlyBigScreen":true,"commonData":{"dashWidth":100,"actWidth":1300,"fontSize":"2rem","dashHeight":"2.7rem","labelsOnSide":true},"data":["Some plants grow really tall and have hard, thick, brown, and woody stems. Their branches typically start higher up on the stem and away from the ground. These plants are called *trees*. \nSome plants are typically small with soft and green stems. These are known as *herbs*.\nSome plants have hard stems but not very thick. These are known as *shrubs*.\nSome plants with weak stems need support to climb and grow, and are called *climbers*. Some plants creep along the ground and are called *creepers*.","The thin lines on the leaves of the plants are called *veins*. The pattern of veins on the leaf is called *venation*.\nIn some leaves, you can observe a net-like pattern of veins on both sides of a thick middle vein. This pattern is called *reticulate* venation.\nIn some leaves, you may observe that the veins run parallel. This pattern is called *parallel* venation.\n","Soak some chickpea and maize seeds in water for three days. Remove the seed *coat* and observe the structure.  \nChickpea seeds are split into 2 parts. Each part is called a *cotyledon* . Plants that have seeds with two cotyledons are called *dicotyledons*, or shortly *dicots*. Maize has a single thin cotyledon. Plants with such seeds are called *monocotyledons*, or shortly *monocots*.\n","Dicot plants have *reticulate* venation and *taproot* system.\nMonocot plants have *parallel* venation and a *fibrous* root system.","The special features that enable plants and animals to survive in a particular region are called *adaptations*. \nThe place where plants and animals live is called their *habitat*.\nLiving things that live on land are said to live in *terrestrial* habitats.\nLiving things that live in water are said to live in *aquatic* habitats.\nLiving things that can live in both land and water are called *amphibians*.\n"]},{"id":"mcq","label":"Multiple Choice Questions","type":"mcq","data":{"questions":[{"qText":"Plants that are usually not big and not small are called ______.","options":"shrubs, herbs, trees"},{"qText":"Herbs usually have ____ colored stem.","options":"green, brown, gray"},{"qText":"The plant that bears watermelon is a ","options":"creeper, climber, shrub"},{"qText":"Dicot plants have ","options":"reticulate venation and taproot system\nparallel venation and a fibrous root system\nreticulate venation and fibrous root system\nparallel venation and a taproot system"},{"qText":"Monocot plants have","options":"parallel venation and a fibrous root system\nreticulate venation and taproot system\nreticulate venation and fibrous root system\nparallel venation and a taproot system"},{"qText":"Animals that can live in both land and water are called","options":"amphibians\nterrestrial animals\naquatic animals"}]}},{"label":"Complete Word","type":"completeWord","id":"complete-word","data":{"text":"The thin lines on the leaves of the plants. | VEINS | _____\nThe pattern of veins on the leaf  | VENATION \nSmall plants with soft and green stems | HERBS | _____\nPlants with hard stems, but not as big as a tree | SHRUBS | ______\nPlants that creep along the ground  | CREEPERS | ______RS\nThe root system with one main root and many small side roots | TAPROOT | _______\nThe root system with a bunch of similar-sized thin roots arising from the base of the stem is called _______ roots | FIBROUS | _______\nThe damage to habitats of plants and animals results in loss of their homes, food, and other resources. This leads to the loss of ________. | BIODIVERSITY"}},{"label":"True or False","id":"true-false","type":"classifySentence","data":{"title":"Classify the below sentences as true and false","types":[{"name":"True","text":"Monocots plants have parallel venation.\nThe fleshy stems of desert plants store the water."},{"name":"False","text":"Dicots plants have fibrous root.\nTerrestrial animals cannot swim in water.\nSacred groves are forests created by humans to protect the habitats. | They are naturally formed and protected by humans.\nCamels are found only in hot deserts."}]}},{"label":"Terrestrial vs Aquatic habitats","id":"classify","type":"group","data":{"title":"Classify the below habitats as Terrestrial or Aquatic.","types":[{"name":"Terrestrial","text":"Forests, Deserts, Grasslands, Mountains"},{"name":"Aquatic","text":"Ponds, Lakes, Rivers, Oceans"}]}},{"id":"notes-2","type":"passage","label":"Notes: The two camels of India","data":{"title":"The two camels of India","text":"If we think about camels, we remember hot desert like the Thar desert in the state of Rajasthan. But do you know, they are also found in very cold place like Ladakh? Deserts are places that receive very little rainfall. There are two types of deserts: hot and cold deserts.\nThe camel of the hot desert has long legs with wide hooves. They help them to walk on the sandy desert without sinking into the sand. \nOn the other hand, the height and legs of camels of a cold desert are comparatively shorter. These short legs allow them to walk easily in mountainous regions. \nIn deserts, food is not available easily. Camels store food in their humps. Camels found in the hot desert have single hump. It helps them to survive during the scarcity of food.\nCold desert camels have two humps for the same purpose. Also, they grow long hair from head to neck, which protect them in the cold winters.\n"}},{"id":"cooking-old-new","type":"slides2","label":"Two types of leaves,roots, seeds","data":{"title":"Two types of leaves,roots, seeds","displayType":"steps","images":"img/science/big/diversity-world-6","imgHeight":400,"fontSize":"1.5rem","steps":[{"text":"The thin lines on the leaves are called veins. The pattern of veins on the leaf is called venation. If the veins run parallel, it is called parallel venation. eg: banana plant, grass.","img":"parallel-venation"},{"text":"Some leaves have a thick middle vein, and a net-like pattern of veins on both sides. This  pattern is called reticulate venation. eg: hibiscus plant, mango tree, papaya tree, peepal tree.","img":"reticulate"},{"text":"Some plants have one main root and small side roots arising from it. The main root is called taproot. eg: mustard plant, hibiscus, chickpea","img":"tap-root"},{"text":"Some plants have a bunch of similar-sized thin roots arising from the base of the stem.  Such roots are called fibrous roots. eg: common grass, wheat","img":"fibrous-root"},{"text":"Chickpea seeds are split into 2 parts. Each part is called a cotyledon. Plants that have seeds with two cotyledons are called dicotyledons, or shortly dicots.","img":"dicot"},{"text":"Maize has a single thin cotyledon. These type of plants are called monocotyledons, or shortly monocots.","img":"monocot"}]}},{"id":"adaptation-slides","type":"slides2","label":"Adaptation in plants & animals","data":{"title":"Adaptation in plants & animals","displayType":"steps","images":"img/science/big/diversity-world-6","imgHeight":400,"fontSize":"1.5rem","steps":[{"text":"Extreme cold regions experience frequent snowfall. Conical shape and sloping branches of deodar trees enable them to let the snow slide off easily.","img":"deodar-tree"},{"text":"The fleshy stems of plants found in the desert can store water and help them tolerate the hot conditions.","img":"desert-plant"},{"text":"Rhododendron trees have shorter height and smaller leaves to survive through the heavy winds on mountain tops.","img":"rhododendron-tree"},{"text":"Hot desert camels have long legs with wide hooves. They help them to walk on the sandy desert without sinking into the sand.","img":"thar-camel"},{"text":"Cold desert camels have short legs that allow them to walk easily in mountainous regions. They grow long hair from head to neck, which protect them in the cold winters.","img":"ladakh-camel"},{"text":"Polar bears accumulate a lot of fat under their skin. This fat serves as an energy source. It supports them during their months-long winter sleep (hibernation), enabling them to survive without eating.","img":"polarbear"}]}}]}